@amishas157 

In general, let's try to be compatible with the GNU standards for command line options here: https://www.gnu.org/prep/standards/html_node/Option-Table.html#Option-Table. What you've sketched will be fine with one change: `--resource-type` for `--resource_type`. We've got precedent in `mapbox geocode` for `-t` as a short name for `--place-type` and so we can use `-t` here as a shortcut for `--resource-type`.

Commands get their access token from their "context" like this: https://github.com/mapbox/mapbox-cli-py/blob/master/mapboxcli/scripts/geocoding.py#L97. You won't have to write any other code to get it from the command line.

