@SamLau95 these (non-breaking) changes may be relevant for this summer's Data 8.

The addition of `group_barh` will simplify some code slightly and allow you to talk about `barh` before `group`, if you want.

The addition of grouping to `hist` might open up some cross-categorization examples that were previously too cumbersome to use.  Note that it produces the conditional distribution of each group, not the marginal; that means that each group's histogram sums to 1, rather than to the proportion of rows in the original table that are in the group.

